race.comment: MASSIRA (9) underrated gelding who got under the guard from the wide gate last start when covering ground for a tough win over 1000m at this track in Highway company. Gets a more economical run today and expected to measure up again. Top each way prospect. HAWKER HALL (2) improving sprinter building a solid winning CV. Kept fresh after holding off all challengers when saluting over this trip at Rosehill. Since fitted with a trial win over 845m at Wyong. Will prove hard to run down with the sharp rise in weight. CANDLEWICK (7) resumes after she raced without luck at Group level over the Queensland winter. Undefeated first-up and regular rider stays aboard. Genuine top-three prospect. GATSBY'S (1) unreliable gelding having his first start for the Pride yard. Fitted with the two trials and look for him late in this weaker race.
